body:
I have found why the bug occurs. Within `to_absolute` the internal function `_get_freq` is used to obtain the frequency which is then given to the conversion. The `_get_freq` function is:

```python
def _get_freq(x):
    """Get unit for conversion of time deltas to integer."""
    if hasattr(x, "freqstr"):
        if x.freqstr is None:
            return None
        elif "-" in x.freqstr:
           return x.freqstr.split("-")[0]
        else:
            return x.freqstr
    else:
        return None
```

So in the case of this bug we have `freqstr = "W-WED"` but the `_get_freq` function only returns "W" which then defaults back to "W-SUN" hence the error. This could be easily fixed by removing the case distinction for "-" in the `freqstr` however I imagine it is there for a reason, @fkiraly @mloning do you know why this case distinction is needed?
